# LGLC Website Templates - Aider AI Rules

This project uses a token-based design system. Follow these rules strictly.

## CSS Rules

### Design Tokens - MANDATORY
- ALWAYS use design tokens from `css/design-tokens.css` via `var(--token-name)`
- NEVER hardcode CSS values (no `16px`, `#ED1C24`, `8px`, etc.)
- NEVER use raw `px` for spacing, fonts, or sizes (use tokens with `rem` values)
- Import `css/design-tokens.css` FIRST before any component CSS
- Each component gets its own CSS file in `css/` directory

### Correct CSS Example:
```css
.component {
  padding: var(--spacing-4);
  color: var(--color-primary-red);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
}
```

### Incorrect CSS Example:
```css
.component {
  padding: 16px;        /* WRONG - use var(--spacing-4) */
  color: #ED1C24;      /* WRONG - use var(--color-primary-red) */
  border-radius: 8px;  /* WRONG - use var(--border-radius-md) */
}
```

## Design Token Reference

### Colors
- Primary: `--color-primary-red`, `--color-primary-navy`, `--color-primary-yellow`, `--color-primary-black`
- Semantic: `--text-primary`, `--text-secondary`, `--text-tertiary`, `--text-inverse`
- Backgrounds: `--bg-page`, `--bg-surface`, `--bg-elevated`

### Spacing
- Use `--spacing-1` through `--spacing-24` (never hardcode spacing)

### Typography
- Font sizes: `--font-size-xs` through `--font-size-5xl`
- Font weights: `--font-weight-normal` through `--font-weight-extrabold`
- Line heights: `--line-height-tight`, `--line-height-normal`, `--line-height-relaxed`

### Borders & Shadows
- Border radius: `--border-radius-sm` through `--border-radius-2xl`
- Shadows: `--shadow-xs` through `--shadow-2xl`

## HTML Rules

- Use semantic HTML5: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- No inline styles - all CSS in stylesheets
- Import CSS order: `design-tokens.css` first, then component CSS

## JavaScript Rules

- Vanilla JavaScript only (no frameworks)
- Ensure accessibility: keyboard navigation, ARIA updates, focus management
- Component-specific JS in `js/` directory

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: default styles for mobile, enhance for larger screens
- Breakpoints: `48rem` (tablet), `64rem` (desktop), `80rem` (large desktop)
- CSS variables cannot be used in `@media` queries - use values directly:

```css
@media (min-width: 48rem) {  /* --breakpoint-md */
  /* Tablet styles */
}
```

## Accessibility

- Focus: Yellow outline (`--color-primary-yellow`) with offset
- Touch targets: Minimum `var(--touch-target-min)` (2.75rem/44px)
- All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Include ARIA labels and logical tab order

## Component Creation

1. Create new CSS file in `css/` directory
2. Reference tokens via `var(--token-name)`
3. If new token needed, add to `css/design-tokens.css` first
4. Follow patterns in `css/header.css` and `css/footer.css`

## File Structure

```
css/
  design-tokens.css    # MUST be imported first
  header.css
  footer.css
  [component].css      # One file per component
js/
  [component].js       # Component-specific JS
```

## Common Mistakes - AVOID

1. Hardcoding CSS values
2. Using `px` for spacing/fonts
3. Defining custom values in component CSS
4. Wrong CSS import order
5. Inline styles
6. Missing accessibility features

